EXTRA_ACCESSORY_SUPPORTS_HISTORY

static final java.lang.String EXTRA_ACCESSORY_SUPPORTS_HISTORY
This Intent-extra is used when the settings of an extension is to be displayed by means of starting the activity defined in the Registration.ExtensionColumns.CONFIGURATION_ACTIVITY of the extension. The Intent-extra is only valid for extensions that support the Notification API. This extra indicates if the accessory supports showing notifications history.

The value can be true (default) or false. If false, the accessory does not support showing the history of notifications and a notification extension might want to hide e.g. "Clear history" from its settings
